        50 Comment by jc — July 19, 2011 @ 10:51 pm

    It seems that a good place to start is with the set, A, of ordered pairs of points, with each ordered pair representing a “transition” from one pivot point to the next. Each member of A would be a vertex in a directed graph containing an edge from each “transition” to its successor “transition”.

    One would then need to show that a cycle exists in this graph for which every point participates in at least one (actually two) of the vertices.
     
